Of the latter I send with this a fruit. Of the Kei apple (
   Aberia Caffra
) I have already sent to you a supply of seeds; but I shall forward a few more with this. lt has this advantage over the other, that the preserved fruit, or rather a jelly prepared from the fruit, imparts to the rind of pumpkins, water-melons, and similar fruits, the flavour of fresh apples, when mixed with these in small quantities and cooked.
